My favorite Love Story 🤎

We recently shared with you guys on our YouTube Channel that we started going to marriage counseling! As many of you know we’ve been together 11 years & it wasn’t until recently that we started having petty arguments & it started to get BAD!!

So, fast forward - Part of us moving into a new place was to have a fresh start and reset! Our last place was opened up to bad energy & we feel like part of that was the reason for most of the previous problems in our marriage! 

If anyone knows me, y’all know I’m big on removing myself from a negative space. We’re most definitely making it a goal to continue protecting the place we lay our heads from this point on… 

 I’m just so happy 🤎 Marriage can be so beautiful when you both are willing to give it your all!

Happy Sunday 🤎 #Blessed

“Just because things aren’t being done your way doesn’t mean they’re being done wrong.”

And honestly at that specific moment, I realized that I’d been caring more about things being done my way, instead of just being appreciative of the wholehearted, unconditional, loving support system that I have no matter what (my family)! Or that I cared more about the way the kids cleaned up instead of the fact that they were innocently trying to clean up behind themselves or practice the life skills they’d been taught. Or maybe even that I cared more about the verbiage my wife used when she sent a response for me instead of the fact that out of genuine care, she wanted to make sure I was still verbally present even while I was physically absent.

This roller coaster of truth hit me right in the gut and emphasized the fact that no victory, or progress matters if the process to get there was filled with negativity, anger, impatience, or even judgement.

It’s almost as if I’d been stuck in the cycle of unhappiness within, disappointment throughout, and dead end stubbornness when I was wrong the whole time 😂 imagine that!

- All because I was more focused on how things around me got done or how i perceived the end result than the only ones that were helping me, depending on me, and learning from me.

Undoubtably it’s way past time to begin to change my behavior, take more deep breaths, recognize that the problem is ME, not anyone else in my home, not anyone else in my life! This work can only be done from the inside out, before I can even remotely expect anything from anyone else. 

To all the Fathers, Husbands, & Spouses who come across this; - Take into consideration that we set the tone for our homes, lives, and families WAY
MORE than we realize. Majority of times, it’s not “kids who just don’t understand” or “nobody knows how to do anything right,” IT’S AS SIMPLE AS US CONSTANTLY PRODUCING THESE FAR-FETCHED EXPECTATIONS THAT DON’T AMOUNT TO ANYTHING!
